-- Total Agrees to Pay $1.74 Billion for Stakes in Suncor Projects in Canada
-- B y   V i d y a   R o o t
-- 2010-12-17T07:24:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-17/total-pays-suncor-1-74-billion-for-stakes-in-fort-hills-voyageur-joslyn.html
Total SA said it will pay 1.75
billion Canadian dollars for stakes in several Suncor projects.
It said in an e-mailed statement that it raised its stake in
Fort Hills to 39 percent and bought a 49 percent stake in the
Voyageur upgrader project. The oil company also bought 38.25
percent stake in Joslyn.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vidya Root at 
 vroot@bloomberg.net  